<B>Dreamsicle Cookies</B><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Dry ingredients:<BR>
1/2 cup Tang instant breakfast powder<BR>
3/4 cup sugar<BR>
1 3/4 cups flour mixed with<BR>
 1/2 teaspoon baking powder<BR>
 1/2 teaspoon baking sugar<BR>
<BR>
1 1/2 cup vanilla chips<BR>
1 stick (1/4 lb) butter or margarine - VERY SOFT<BR>
1 egg, slightly beaten<BR>
1 teaspoon vanilla<BR>
<BR>
1.  Mix dry ingredients well.<BR>
2.  Add the butter, egg and vanilla<BR>
3.  Mix until completely blended.  Add vanilla chips, then finish mixing with your  
     hands.<BR>
4.  Shape into balls the size of walnuts.  Place 2" apart on a sprayed baking           
     sheet.<BR>
5.  Bake at 375  for 12-14 minutes until tops are very lightly browned.  Cool<BR>
     for 5 minutes before removing.<BR>
